        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3849955559" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13903856301531717374">My father grew up in the same area that Kooser did, so reading these simple tales of his family feel a bit like my own. Partly due to my connection and largely due to the colorful language, I can imagine these scenes with such poignancy. This reads slow in the most wonderful way and floats freely between prose and poetry. There is something about Guttenberg, and any small town along the upper Mississippi, that feels like a secret; a simplicity of joy that you never quite fully realize but the me</span>
  <span id="freeText13903856301531717374" style="display:none">My father grew up in the same area that Kooser did, so reading these simple tales of his family feel a bit like my own. Partly due to my connection and largely due to the colorful language, I can imagine these scenes with such poignancy. This reads slow in the most wonderful way and floats freely between prose and poetry. There is something about Guttenberg, and any small town along the upper Mississippi, that feels like a secret; a simplicity of joy that you never quite fully realize but the mere thought of it feels a bit like a balloon in your chest or a warm breeze on your face. </span>
  <a data-text-id="13903856301531717374" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

