<div id="review_2524300518" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2524300518" />
    <a title="Candace Haskell" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/27753718-candace-haskell"><img alt="Candace Haskell" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1456682992p2/27753718.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2524300518?book_show_action=true">Dec 04, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Candace Haskell" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Candace Haskell" href="/user/show/27753718-candace-haskell">Candace Haskell</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/27753718-candace-haskell?shelf=2018-books-read">2018-books-read</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2524300518" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15249298987324113705">This book is an evocative, prose love letter about the poet&apos;s Midwestern family roots. Kooser wanted to honor his mother&apos;s people from Iowa and also name and claim the attitudes from an era of people who accepted life as it came and took care of their own, especially Uncle Elvy, suffering from cerebral palsy and simply incorporated into the family, not farmed out for care. Kooser&apos;s grandfather, being medically evaluated late in life, apparently had a burst appendix as a boy - and simply endured </span>
  <span id="freeText15249298987324113705" style="display:none">This book is an evocative, prose love letter about the poet's Midwestern family roots. Kooser wanted to honor his mother's people from Iowa and also name and claim the attitudes from an era of people who accepted life as it came and took care of their own, especially Uncle Elvy, suffering from cerebral palsy and simply incorporated into the family, not farmed out for care. Kooser's grandfather, being medically evaluated late in life, apparently had a burst appendix as a boy - and simply endured and survived it. These are hard-working people with a love of their hard-scrabble land and lives that Kooser captures and saves for all of us.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15249298987324113705" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


