<div id="review_4222789091" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4222789091" />
    <a title="Lynda Huffman" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/87210296-lynda-huffman"><img alt="Lynda Huffman" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4222789091?book_show_action=true">Sep 06, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lynda Huffman" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lynda Huffman" href="/user/show/87210296-lynda-huffman">Lynda Huffman</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4222789091" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18342697705296138439">Sixty wonderful pages! A very moving memoir of the author’s maternal family that had me taking my own trip down memory lane. The writing is almost poetic in its beauty (appropriately so, as the author is a Pulitzer Prize winning poet) and paints a vivid picture of small town life in Iowa 70 years ago. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


