<div id="review_100305502" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/100305502" />
    <a title="Robert Isenberg" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/695451-robert-isenberg"><img alt="Robert Isenberg" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1447004568p2/695451.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/100305502?book_show_action=true">Apr 27, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Robert Isenberg" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Robert Isenberg" href="/user/show/695451-robert-isenberg">Robert Isenberg</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer100305502" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11354075178270928040">I love poetry, and I can enjoy remembrances of things past -- to a point. Kooser crosses my threshold of patience. Nothing really &quot;happens.&quot; I kept confusing characters, in-between unexpected naps. The floral metaphors were positively bullying, as if to say, &quot;DID YOU NOTICE? I&apos;M A METAPHOR! LOOK AT ME, LOOK AT ME!&quot; For such a short volume, &quot;Lights&quot; will cure many nights of insomnia.</span>
  <span id="freeText11354075178270928040" style="display:none">I love poetry, and I can enjoy remembrances of things past -- to a point. Kooser crosses my threshold of patience. Nothing really "happens." I kept confusing characters, in-between unexpected naps. The floral metaphors were positively bullying, as if to say, "DID YOU NOTICE? I'M A METAPHOR! LOOK AT ME, LOOK AT ME!" For such a short volume, "Lights" will cure many nights of insomnia.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11354075178270928040" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


